# Creekside Website Development Rules

## Component Usage Rules

### 1. Common Components Must Be Used
- **ALWAYS** use components from `src/components/ui/` for UI elements (Button, SectionHeading, PillarCard, etc.)
- **ALWAYS** use components from `src/components/layout/` for layout elements (Navbar, Footer, PreFooter)
- **NEVER** recreate UI components inline in page files
- **NEVER** duplicate component logic across pages

### 2. Page Structure Requirements
- All pages MUST use `BaseLayout.astro` or appropriate layout component
- All pages MUST import and use common UI components from `src/components/ui/`
- Page-specific sections should be in `src/sections/[page-name]/` directory
- Shared sections should be in `src/components/sections/`

### 3. Import Patterns
- Use absolute imports from `src/components/` when possible
- Example: `import Button from '@components/ui/Button.astro'`
- Example: `import Navbar from '@components/layout/Navbar.astro'`

### 4. Constants Usage
- **ALWAYS** import colors, navigation links, and data from `src/constants/`
- **NEVER** hardcode color values, navigation items, or data in page files
- Use: `import { COLORS, NAV_LINKS, PILLARS } from '@constants'`

### 5. Component Composition
- Pages should compose sections, not contain inline markup
- Each section should be a separate component file
- Sections should use common UI components internally

### 6. File Organization
- Page files: `src/pages/[page-name]/index.astro` or `src/pages/[page-name].astro`
- Section files: `src/sections/[page-name]/[SectionName].astro`
- UI components: `src/components/ui/[ComponentName].astro`
- Layout components: `src/components/layout/[ComponentName].astro`

### 7. Code Reusability
- If a component is used in 2+ places, it MUST be in `src/components/`
- If a section is page-specific but complex, it should be in `src/sections/[page-name]/`
- If a section is used across multiple pages, it should be in `src/components/sections/`

### 8. Prohibited Patterns
- ❌ Inline component definitions in page files
- ❌ Duplicate component logic across files
- ❌ Hardcoded colors, navigation items, or data
- ❌ Creating new UI components when existing ones can be used
- ❌ Bypassing layout components

### 9. Required Patterns
- ✅ Import and use Button from `@components/ui/Button.astro`
- ✅ Import and use SectionHeading from `@components/ui/SectionHeading.astro`
- ✅ Import and use Navbar/Footer from `@components/layout/`
- ✅ Import constants from `@constants`
- ✅ Use BaseLayout or appropriate layout wrapper
- ✅ Break complex pages into section components

### 10. Example Page Structure
```astro
---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Button from '@components/ui/Button.astro';
import SectionHeading from '@components/ui/SectionHeading.astro';
import HeroSection from '@sections/home/HeroSection.astro';
import { COLORS, NAV_LINKS } from '@constants';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <HeroSection />
  <section>
    <SectionHeading>Title</SectionHeading>
    <Button variant="primary">Action</Button>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
```

## Enforcement
- When creating or editing page files, ensure all common components are imported and used
- When creating new components, check if similar functionality exists in `src/components/` first
- Refactor inline components to use common components when found
